### The Generic List

While arrays have a fixed size, `List<T>` can grow dynamically. It is the most commonly used collection in C#.

You declare it by specifying the **Type** inside the angle brackets `< >`. Then, you can use the `.Add()` method to insert items.

**Example:**
```csharp
var names = new List<string>();
names.Add("Alice");
names.Add("Bob");
```
Alternatively, you can use a **collection initializer** to add items right when you create it:
```csharp
var names = new List<string> { "Alice", "Bob" };
```

