### if / else

The `if` statement lets your program **branch** based on a condition. You can chain multiple conditions with `else if`, and provide a fallback with `else`.

```csharp
int score = 85;
if (score >= 90)
    Console.WriteLine("A");
else if (score >= 80)
    Console.WriteLine("B");
else
    Console.WriteLine("C");
// Output: B
```

C# also has a **ternary operator** for compact one-line decisions:
```csharp
string result = (score >= 60) ? "Pass" : "Fail";
```

