### Loops

Loops let you execute a block of code repeatedly.

**`for` loop** – best when you know how many iterations you need:
```csharp
for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
    Console.WriteLine(i);   // 0, 1, 2
```

**`foreach` loop** – iterates over every element in a collection:
```csharp
var names = new List<string> { "Alice", "Bob" };
foreach (var name in names)
    Console.WriteLine(name);
```

**`while` loop** – repeats as long as a condition is true:
```csharp
int n = 3;
while (n > 0)
{
    Console.WriteLine(n);
    n--;
}
```

