### Methods

A **method** is a block of code that performs a task. It can accept **parameters** and **return** a value.

```csharp
public class MathHelper
{
    public int Add(int a, int b)
    {
        return a + b;
    }
}
var m = new MathHelper();
Console.WriteLine(m.Add(3, 4));  // 7
```

The **return type** appears before the method name. Use `void` when the method doesn't return anything:
```csharp
public void SayHello(string name)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Hello, {name}!");
}
```

