### JSON Serialization with System.Text.Json

**Serialize** — turn a C# object into a JSON string:
```csharp
var person = new { Name = "Alice", Age = 30 };
string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person);
// {"Name":"Alice","Age":30}
```

**Deserialize** — parse a JSON string back into a C# object:
```csharp
public class Person { public string Name { get; set; } public int Age { get; set; } }
var p = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Person>(json);
```

`System.Text.Json` is the built-in, high-performance JSON library in modern .NET.

