### IDisposable & using

Some objects hold **unmanaged resources** (file handles, network connections, etc.) that the garbage collector cannot clean up automatically. These types implement `IDisposable`, which has a single method: `Dispose()`.

The **`using` block** guarantees `Dispose()` is called, even if an exception occurs:
```csharp
using (var resource = new MyResource())
{
    resource.DoWork();
} // Dispose() called automatically here
```

C# 8 introduced the simpler **`using` declaration**:
```csharp
using var resource = new MyResource();
resource.DoWork();
// Dispose() called at end of scope
```

