### Extension Methods

An **extension method** lets you add new methods to an existing type without modifying it. Under the hood, it is simply a **static method** in a **static class** whose first parameter is marked with `this`:

```csharp
public static class StringHelper
{
    public static string Shout(this string s)
    {
        return s.ToUpper() + "!";
    }
}
// Now you can call it like an instance method:
// "hello".Shout()  →  "HELLO!"
```

Even without the `this` keyword, the pattern of **static utility classes** is extremely common in C#:
```csharp
Console.WriteLine(StringHelper.Shout("hello")); // HELLO!
```

