### Inheritance

**Inheritance** lets a class reuse all the members of another class. The child (derived) class uses `:` to inherit from a parent (base) class:

```csharp
public class Animal
{
    public virtual string Speak() { return "..."; }
}
public class Dog : Animal
{
    public override string Speak() { return "Woof"; }
}
```

Mark a base method `virtual` to allow overriding. Use `override` in the derived class to replace the behaviour.

