### Abstract Classes

An **abstract class** cannot be instantiated directly — it exists only as a base for other classes. Methods marked `abstract` have **no body**; every derived class **must** provide an implementation.

```csharp
public abstract class Shape
{
    public abstract double Area();
}
public class Circle : Shape
{
    public double Radius { get; set; }
    public override double Area() => Math.PI * Radius * Radius;
}
```

Use abstract classes when you want to guarantee that all subclasses share a common interface but each provides its own logic.

