### Interfaces

An **interface** defines a contract — a set of methods and properties a class must implement. Unlike abstract classes, a class can implement **multiple** interfaces.

```csharp
public interface IGreeter
{
    string Greet(string name);
}
public class HelloGreeter : IGreeter
{
    public string Greet(string name) => $"Hello, {name}!";
}
```

Interfaces are the backbone of **dependency injection** and **testable** architecture. You program against the interface, not the concrete class.

