### Pattern Matching

C# lets you test a value against patterns in powerful ways.

**Type pattern** with `is`:
```csharp
object obj = 42;
if (obj is int n)
    Console.WriteLine($"Integer: {n}");
```

**Switch expression** — a compact alternative to switch statements:
```csharp
string Classify(int n) => n switch
{
    > 0 => "Positive",
    < 0 => "Negative",
    _   => "Zero"
};
```

The `_` is the **discard pattern** — it matches anything not already handled.

